    "• 𝜇 𝑖 = 𝜇𝑡 𝑖 represents the expected count for each entity after elapsed time, 𝑡 𝑖.",
    "• 𝛼 denotes the dispersion parameter of the distribution.",
    "The expected count 𝜇 𝑖 at time 𝑡 𝑖 is determined using Negative Binomial Regression as:",
    "• 𝑡 𝑖, is the relative elapsed time, centered around the mean year of the study period to address multicollinearity, reducing the correlation between the time variable and its interaction terms in the model.",
    "• 𝛽 0 is the intercept, representing the baseline log count."
